OL,4,Cpensioner 'motivated by conflict in
OL,5,CGaza'
OL,7,F"In particular, Mr Nouri had reported
OL,8,Fthe defendant to the police and those
OL,9,Fresponsible for managing their
OL,10,Faccommodation.
OL,12,F"Second, Mr Nouri was a Muslim who had
OL,13,Fconverted to Christianity, and the
OL,14,Fdefendant would therefore have
OL,15,Fregarded him as an apostate or
OL,16,F'murtad'.
OL,18,F"Third, when the defendant was
OL,19,Finterviewed by the police, he
OL,20,Finitially thought that he had killed
OL,21,Fboth Mr Nouri and Mr Carney.
OL,26,@oD@AOUtD@AOUzD@AOU
